Put a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{0.5%tsp} on to boil for the potatoes. Chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!). When boiling add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim the @spring onion{1} then slice thinly. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a garlic press). Drain and rinse the @lentils{1} in a #sieve{}. Trim the @carrot{1}, then quarter lengthways (no need to peel). Chop widthways into small pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Add the @vivera plant chicken pieces{175%g} and carrot pieces. Fry until golden for ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add the lentils, @wholegrain mustard{1} and water (see ingredients for amount), and stir to combine, allow to simmer until the carrots are tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Stir in the @soured cream{150}. Add the @baby spinach{100} in handfuls and cook until wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Once cooked, drain the potatoes in a #colander{} and return to the pan off the heat. Add a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @milk{?splash} and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in two thirds of the spring onion. Cover with a #lid{}.

Divide the mash between plates. Top the mash with the creamy fricassee and sprinkle with remaining spring onion. Enjoy!